    "dct:title": "YAGO",
    "dct:description": " YAGO is described as a lightweight, extensible ontology that integrates entities and relations, combining high coverage with high accuracy. The dataset contains approximately 900,000 entities and five million facts, including both taxonomic (Is-A hierarchy) and non-taxonomic relations such as hasWonPrize. It is automatically constructed from Wikipedia and WordNet using a combination of rule-based and heuristic methods. YAGO extends WordNet by introducing entities such as people, organizations, and products, achieving an estimated 95% empirical fact accuracy. It is built on a logically decidable model compatible with RDFS semantics, supporting extensibility through modern information extraction techniques. ",
